triggerConfigs.label: API Trigger - GCS to SFTP
triggerConfigs.description: See the input variable PubSubPayload's default value for an example payload that GCS will send to PubSub.  Change the default value to your test bucket and object to make it easier to Test from the Integration TEST button

triggerConfigs.label: Copy File from SFTP to GCS
triggerConfigs.description: Pass in the full FilePath to the SFTP filename using the input variable : SFTP-FilePath for this API Trigger. This integration will download the file from the SFTP server, and then upload it to GCS.  It is set for ASCII files, so if you have binary, you will need to change a few settings.

triggerConfigs.label: PubSub GCS Notification Trigger
triggerConfigs.description:
Use the GCS Notification feature to notify PubSub when a new Object is created in a bucket.  It's available via GCloud commands only (not in the UI). 
Fill in BUCKET_NAME and TOPIC_NAME in this gcloud command to set up notifications.:

gcloud storage buckets notifications create gs://BUCKET_NAME --topic=TOPIC_NAME

Docs: https://cloud.google.com/storage/docs/reporting-changes#command-line
